<exercise checkit-seed="0041" checkit-slug="M3" checkit-title="Invertible matrices">
  <statement>
    <p>Explain why the matrix <m>A= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; -3 &amp; -6 &amp; 8 \\
-1 &amp; 2 &amp; 5 &amp; -8 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; -3 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 2 &amp; -3
\end{array}\right] </m> is or is not invertible.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer><p><me>\operatorname{RREF} \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; -3 &amp; -6 &amp; 8 \\
-1 &amp; 2 &amp; 5 &amp; -8 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; -3 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 2 &amp; -3
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; -1 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 3 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; -3 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] </me></p><m>A</m> is not invertible.</answer>
</exercise>

